definition: irradiation is a process by which a material entity is exposed to radiative energy, which could be ionizing radiation (such as gamma rays or X-rays)  or not such as UV light or microwaves
An assay that determines gene expression and transcription activity using ribonucleic acids collected from a material entity.
A DNA-microarray is a microarray that is used as a physical 2D immobilisation matrix for DNA sequences. DNA microarray-bound DNA fragments are used as targets for a hybridising probed sample.

studies.description: Transcriptional profiling of human lymphoblastoid TK6 cells comparing mock irradiaed cells resuspended in fresh untreated RPMI 1640 medium with cells resuspended in medium activated by exposure to 2.5 Gy HZE (1 GeV/amu iron ions accelerated at the NASA Space Research Laboratory (NSRL) of Brookhaven National Laboratory). Two-condition experiment, mock irradiated vs. cells exposed to activated medium. 3 biological replicates were independently grown and harvested during three different runs at the NSRL. One replicate per array.

protocols.description: Hybridization was carried out with active mixing using the MAUI Hybridization System (BioMicro Systems, Salt Lake City, UT) for 16 hours in Deposition Hybridization Buffer (Agilent) at 65oC in the presence of the blockers human CoT1, yeast tRNA and poly dA.  Hybridized slides were washed at room temperature once in 0.5X SSC, 0.01% SDS for 5 minutes and again in 0.06X SSC for 5 minutes.

protocols.description: HZE particle irradiation was performed at the NASA Space Radiation Laboratory (NSRL) at Brookhaven National Laboratory.  Exponentially growing cells were concentrated by centrifugation and exposed to graded doses of 1 GeV/amu 56Fe ions (150 keV/Œºm) in a volume of 10 ml per culture point to limit the amount of medium activated during the irradiation.  Dosimetry was performed by the NSRL Physics Group.  Tubes containing the cells were placed perpendicular to the beam in the center of the field, where the variation in fluence was <5%. Control cultures were prepared in the same way and mock irradiated.  An activated-medium control was prepared by irradiating 10 ml of medium without cells to the highest dose used (2.5 Gy).  Immediately after irradiation, medium was added to bring the cells to normal culture densities (4-5 x 105cells/ml).  The cells for the activated control were resuspended in the activated medium prior to addition of the remaining medium.
protocols.name: P-GSE16519-2

protocols.description: RNA was extracted using a modified guanidine thiocyanate method, (Chomczynski and Sacchi, 1987, PMID: 2440339) followed by purification with RNeasy columns (Qiagen, Valencia, CA).  RNA samples were quantified using a Nanodrop spectrophotometer and monitored for quality using an Agilent Bioanalyzer prior to labeling for microarray analysis.

protocols.description: Fluorescently labeled cDNA was prepared from mock-irradiated control and activated medium control whole-cell RNA by a single round of reverse transcription (BRL Superscript II) in the presence of aminoallyl dUTP (Sigma-Aldrich), followed by coupling to monofunctional NHS-ester Cy3 or Cy5 dye (Amersham) (Amundson and Fornace, 2004. PMID:14970650)
